media.description: I could not be happier to announce that this caring, smart, thoughtful, strong, beautiful woman has agreed to be my wife. I have more peace every time I talk to her, more wisdom every time I listen to her, more compassion every time I watch her, and more joy every day I spend with her. I feel overwhelmingly blessed that I will have her by my side throughout this journey of life. My thanks to God, and of course to the precious woman I love, Luesoni.

media.title: Timeline Photos
media.description:
Last year, my sister Christa was diagnosed with cystic fibrosis (CF). This year, on August 20, there will be a CF fundraising bicycle race in Ann Arbor â the Michigan CF Cycle for Life. 

CF is a genetic disease that affects the lungs and digestive system. There is currently a medley of treatments that target the symptoms of the disease, but there is no definitive treatment or cure. All people with CF face great uncertainty. 

Christa, more than some, benefits from the drugs that are available. She herself will be riding in the Michigan Cycle for Life this August (and beating many of us), which not only speaks to her unassailable enthusiasm, but also demonstrates the potential of CF drug research. 

Because Christa is a compassionate friend, compulsive volunteer, and future physician, the number of people she will help, serve, and heal over her lifetime will inevitably exceed the number of benefactors she will have. If you would like to seize this rare chance to help a person who has devoted herself to helping others, you can donate to any of the riders on our Cycle for Life team â @[1102847763105061:274:Team Sweat Quest]. Your donation will (to Christaâs great relief) benefit not just her, but all CF patients; proceeds go to the Cystic Fibrosis Foundation. Or you can join our team as a cyclist and raise money for your ride. The link to donate or register is below. Spread the word!

http://fightcf.cff.org/goto/teamsweatquest

I'm leaving for the Marshall Islands tomorrow morning. I'll be teaching at a high school there for the next year. I'll have only periodic internet access, and I'm not sure if I'll have a phone at all. I'll maybe use Facebook when I can, but I'll also try to post stuff on the blog listed below. I know it might seem strange that the un-technological Andy Kuck is making a Facebook post about his blog, but I assure you that it really is me (I have refrained from "hashtagging" something so as to not trigger the apocalypse).

Just to let everyone know, I am not an Arsenal fan. My Facebook page was  at the mercy of Andrew Luginbill for an hour, on account of me losing to him in the FIFA video game. And because I don't really know how to work Facebook, I may be unable to ever stop what Andrew set into motion during that hour. Luckily, it looks like I am actually friends with the people Andrew "friended." If you are not my friend, I apologize. Well, here's to hoping I am not posting this where my birthday or blood type or something else should go. Andy

Hey jason. I just wanted to encourage you to like Arsenal. They're great. I'm a HUUUUUUUGGGGGGGGGEEEEEEEE fan. If skip bayless liked soccer he'd be an arsenal fan. love ya lots xxOOXoXooOxxOOxxxxOOOXXXooXo
